			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Our team members challenge the status quo with original thoughts and ideas and follow through with actions, through collaboration and team work.</p>
<p>
We are small enough for each team member to make a valuable contribution and see the immediate impact of their efforts, but also well established with more than 10 years in the mobile social entertainment space.</p>
<p>
At airG, we develop mobile communities and wireless social networking products.&nbsp; We&rsquo;re working with industry leaders such as Verizon, Sprint Nextel, AT&amp;T, Bell Canada and T-Mobile to define an entirely new way of interacting on your mobile phone. In our ideally situated office in the heart of downtown Vancouver, we&rsquo;re creating products that enable millions of customers to experience a sense of being connected. Wirelessly.</p>
<p>
We are in search of an Accountant to join our FINANCE team.</p>
<p>
For this role you will:</p>
<p>
&bull; Oversee and review AP and AR transactions.<br />
&bull; Prepare wire and credit card payments.<br />
&bull; Process online purchases.<br />
&bull; Process payroll and track vacation and sick leaves.<br />
&bull; Assist with the compilation of SRED documentation including timesheets.<br />
&bull; Prepare, file and reconcile HST/GST, VAT, WCB and other statuatory required returns.<br />
&bull; Prepare month end account reconciliations including intercompany balances.<br />
&bull; Prepare working papers for annual financial audits.<br />
&bull; Other duties as required.</p>
<p>
Key Talents:</p>
<p>
&bull; 5 to 7 years of progressive accounting experience.<br />
&bull; Self-starter who possesses excellent interpersonal and communication skills.<br />
&bull; Enthusiasm and willingness to learn.<br />
&bull; Detail orientated and strong organizational skills.<br />
&bull; Team player with strong initiative to assist as required to meet deadlines.<br />
&bull; Strong working knowledge of Excel and Outlook.<br />
&bull; Knowledge of Accpac would be an asset.<br />
&bull; Completion of a recognized accounting program and is currently enrolled in a CMA or CGA program.</p>
<p>
<br />
We offer an attractive and competitive compensation package including a comprehensive benefits plan with a flexible wellness program, and staff purchase plan for mobile devices like the Android, iPhone and Blackberry.</p>
